results.name: Smallest prime ending a complete Cunningham chain of the second kind (2x-1) of length n.
comment: "Complete" means that the chain is not part of a longer chain.
A005603 has the first prime of each chain.
example: a(4)=17041 because 2131,4261,8521,17041 are prime, but the preceding and following numbers (1066,34081) are not.
results.author: _Alexandre Wajnberg_, Sep 04 2005
